 Car Price Prediction with Machine Learning

ðŸ”¶ Problem Statement
      Accurate car price prediction is crucial in today's automotive market. Car buyers and sellers often struggle to determine the fair market price of vehicles due to the influence of numerous features such as brand, mileage, engine power, age, and fuel type. Traditional estimation methods are inconsistent and subjective. This project aims to build a machine learning model that can predict car prices reliably using various car features.

ðŸŽ¯ Objective
      To develop a machine learning model that can accurately predict the price of a car based on multiple features.

      To use regression models for forecasting car prices.

      To understand the impact of each feature (e.g., brand, mileage, horsepower) on car value.

      To demonstrate the real-world application of ML in the automobile industry.

ðŸ“Š Project Summary
      This project uses a dataset containing various features of cars, including brand reputation, horsepower, mileage, car age, and fuel type. After performing data preprocessing, feature engineering, and exploratory data analysis (EDA), a regression model is trained to predict the price of the car. The model is evaluated using metrics such as RÂ² score and Mean Squared Error (MSE). The final model helps consumers and sellers estimate car prices more effectively.

