ðŸ“ˆ Results
    Linear Regression yielded an RÂ² score of ~0.72, meaning 72% of price variability is explained by the model.

    Random Forest improved prediction performance with an RÂ² score of ~0.89.

    Visualizations confirmed strong correlation between car price and features like mileage, brand, and horsepower.

âœ… Conclusion
    This machine learning project successfully demonstrates how regression models can be used to predict car prices based on key features. The Random Forest model provided higher accuracy and better generalization. Such models are valuable tools for:

     Used car sellers to set fair prices

    Buyers to evaluate deals
 
    Dealerships to optimize inventory pricing

    With further improvements (e.g., web deployment, advanced tuning), this model can be integrated into real-world applications.
 
